Dramatic CCTV footage of a hit-and-run incident that occurred on Tuesday in the Johannesburg CBD has surfaced on social media showing the moment a speeding white bakkie hits a female pedestrian and speeds off. In the shocking footage, posted on a Facebook page titled eBlockwatch, the driver of the vehicle is seen turning on the corner of Bree and Gerard Sekoto streets at an accelerated speed before hitting a woman dressed in an orange T-shirt who was crossing the road. The woman was then dragged by the vehicle several metres to much shock from other pedestrians. She has reportedly been taken to Charlotte Maxeke Hospital for treatment. WARNING: The following video contains graphic images.